  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "As such, fine-tuning open-source LLMs may be more viable down the line for lay radiology report generation.",
    "Furthermore, fine-tuning allows opensource models to adapt to domain-or task-specific data.",
    "In the context of healthcare, this allows models to become familiar with medical vocabulary which, in turn, improves the quality of generated lay reports.",
    "Welleck et al. (2022) and Madaan et al. (2023) have shown that, just as humans evaluate and edit their own work, LLMs are not only capable of evaluating and refining their own outputs but also benefit from doing so.",
    "At the same time, lay reports must be readable and maintain factual accuracy."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "Welleck et al. (2022) and Madaan et al. (2023) have shown that, just as humans evaluate and edit their own work, LLMs are not only capable of evaluating and refining their own outputs but also benefit from doing so."
